  <source>University Medicine Greifswald</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to investigate whether the treatment of acute neurodermitis with
      silver-contained textiles is equivalent or more effective to the conservative exogenous
      treatment with a corticosteroid. Secondary aim is to define skin comfortability of the
      textiles.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
